  "body": "<!--\r\n  Note: if the issue is about documentation or the website, please file it at:\r\n  https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/issues/new\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nFeature\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nThere is no any\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\n`useInstance` hook, which returns some sort of component instance id, which can be used instead of `this` in findDOMNode.\r\n```js\r\nfunction Comp(props) {\r\n  let id = useInstance()\r\n  useLayoutEffect(() => console.log(findDOMNode(id)), []) //<div>Hello!</div>, then null on unmount\r\n\r\n  return <div>Hello!</div>\r\n}\r\n```\r\nOn top of that behaviour  can be created `useDOMNode` hook, which is just:\r\n```js\r\nfunction useDOMNode(refOfCb) {\r\n  let id = useInstance()\r\n  useLayoutEffect(() => {\r\n    let n = findDOMNode(id)\r\n    if (typeof refOrCb === 'function') refOrCb(n)\r\n    else refOrCb.current = n\r\n  })\r\n}\r\n```",
